modules.description: This module facilitates converting durations between different time units using a 64-bit unsigned integer to represent nanoseconds, supporting conversions to and from years, days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, and microseconds. It provides both integer and floating-point conversion functions that truncate toward zero, ensuring precise time interval manipulations while rejecting invalid inputs with exceptions. Typical applications include timekeeping systems, scheduling algorithms, or scientific computations requiring exact duration arithmetic across a wide range of units.
